  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n      \t\t\t\t\t\u003cul\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cli id=\"Entry1\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cspan\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ca name=\"entry\" id=\"EntryAnchor\"\u003eanchor\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/a5/a5b2367e9cea3b57b205af7ce9f2729f.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\" title=\"The office building. Image courtesy David Chipperfield Architects\" data-size=\"3000x3825\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cimg srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/a5/a5b2367e9cea3b57b205af7ce9f2729f.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/a5/a5b2367e9cea3b57b205af7ce9f2729f.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/a5/a5b2367e9cea3b57b205af7ce9f2729f.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\" src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/a5/a5b2367e9cea3b57b205af7ce9f2729f.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" title=\"The office building. Image courtesy David Chipperfield Architects\" alt=\"The office building. Image courtesy David Chipperfield Architects\" width=\"514\" height=\"\"/\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe office building. Image courtesy David Chipperfield Architects\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/firms/cover/3821/david-chipperfield-architects\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eDavid Chipperfield Architects\u003c/a\u003e has just completed a three-building scheme for the larger La Confluence master plan in \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/tag/540420/lyon\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eLyon\u003c/a\u003e, France designed by \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/firms/cover/577/herzog-de-meuron\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eHerzog \u0026amp; de Meuron\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/db/db5de6c0bd9ab05988c321c2e09a6dc2.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x806\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/db/db5de6c0bd9ab05988c321c2e09a6dc2.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/db/db5de6c0bd9ab05988c321c2e09a6dc2.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/db/db5de6c0bd9ab05988c321c2e09a6dc2.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/db/db5de6c0bd9ab05988c321c2e09a6dc2.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eView of the office building from one of the garden courtyards. Image: © Simon Menges \u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe program includes a small office building, housing block, and mixed-use tower. The firm tells us each is \u0026#34;shaped by their structure and defined by their simple rectilinear forms yet react to their specific location in different ways.\u0026#34;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/04/04a33339c6460e2fb13eb85a63fbb4b5.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x806\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/04/04a33339c6460e2fb13eb85a63fbb4b5.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/04/04a33339c6460e2fb13eb85a63fbb4b5.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/04/04a33339c6460e2fb13eb85a63fbb4b5.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/04/04a33339c6460e2fb13eb85a63fbb4b5.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eView of the social housing building from one of the garden courtyards. Image: © Simon Menges\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eAll three mirror each other and the other buildings in the plan thanks to the choice of mineral-like materials to cover each of their facades. The three buildings combined offer a gross floor area equal to 30,000 square meters (appx. 323,000 square feet) and were designed especially to enhance their site\u0026#39;s riverfront connection. \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/a9/a93debf3e60e84ab8523e01bafb4514c.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x1311\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/a9/a93debf3e60e84ab8523e01bafb4514c.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/a9/a93debf3e60e84ab8523e01bafb4514c.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/a9/a93debf3e60e84ab8523e01bafb4514c.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/a9/a93debf3e60e84ab8523e01bafb4514c.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eThe mixed-use tower building. Image: © Simon Menges\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eHousing—or at least its possibility—become another critical aspect of the project, as spaces in the office tower have also been designed for potential future conversion into residential accommodation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/35/3599a76874322bbf5f23c5778403f0bc.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x1311\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/35/3599a76874322bbf5f23c5778403f0bc.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/35/3599a76874322bbf5f23c5778403f0bc.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/35/3599a76874322bbf5f23c5778403f0bc.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/35/3599a76874322bbf5f23c5778403f0bc.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eThe river facade of the office building. Image © Simon Menges \u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe main housing block is made from CLT and precast concrete panels. This composition is seen again in the nine-story office building\u0026#39;s arrangement of recessed timber panels along each of its two facades, held in place by in-situ concrete columns. \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9f/9fa12a7277e125624c7ee3e85883218d.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x806\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9f/9fa12a7277e125624c7ee3e85883218d.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9f/9fa12a7277e125624c7ee3e85883218d.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9f/9fa12a7277e125624c7ee3e85883218d.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/9f/9fa12a7277e125624c7ee3e85883218d.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eEntrance of the social housing building. Image: © Simon Menges\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/3f/3fe028b2452b2b6044fdbe3e0679cc18.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x806\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/3f/3fe028b2452b2b6044fdbe3e0679cc18.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/3f/3fe028b2452b2b6044fdbe3e0679cc18.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/3f/3fe028b2452b2b6044fdbe3e0679cc18.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/3f/3fe028b2452b2b6044fdbe3e0679cc18.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eThe entrance lobby of the office building. Image © Simon Menges \u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe mixed-use building features a visual symmetry made by dividing corner windows rising in the lower office component corner balconies in the upper residential floors. The introduction of board marked concrete facade grants a sculptural quality. It also stands as a less dense \u0026#34;gateway\u0026#34; to the plan\u0026#39;s newest quarter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/67/675d61e0491b91a0327a68488643f9ba.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x806\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/67/675d61e0491b91a0327a68488643f9ba.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/67/675d61e0491b91a0327a68488643f9ba.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/67/675d61e0491b91a0327a68488643f9ba.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/67/675d61e0491b91a0327a68488643f9ba.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eA view of the social housing building. Image © Simon Menges \u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/92/92f6d78249cb224629dfe7ff736850c3.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x806\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/92/92f6d78249cb224629dfe7ff736850c3.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/92/92f6d78249cb224629dfe7ff736850c3.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/92/92f6d78249cb224629dfe7ff736850c3.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/92/92f6d78249cb224629dfe7ff736850c3.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eA view towards the office building with the mixed-use tower in the foreground. Image © Simon Menges\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/firms/cover/149978205/aires-mateus\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eAires Mateus\u003c/a\u003e, Atelier Vera, and AIA Architectes also contributed to the La Confluence master plan. The Belgian firm Wirtz International served as the project\u0026#39;s landscape designer.\u003c/p\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cbr clear=\"all\"/\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ca name=\"comments\" id=\"CommentsAnchor\"\u003e \u003c/a\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\t\t\u003c/ul\u003e\n\t  \t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
